trans-unit.source: Certain subclasses of QIODevice, such as QTcpSocket and QProcess, are asynchronous. This means that I/O functions such as write() or read() always return immediately, while communication with the device itself may happen when control goes back to the event loop. trans-unit.source: Clicking on the blue rectangle will cause the onClicked handler of its child MouseArea to be invoked; the event will then be propagated to the MouseArea of the yellow rectangle, causing its own onClicked handler to be invoked.
